            <title>[LU-14105] lfsck shouldn&apos;t LBUG() on disk data</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14105</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;lfsck_namespace_assistant_handler_p1() will LBUG() if file FID is zero, and file name is not &quot;..&quot;, instead it should treat such file as bad dirent and remove it.&lt;/p&gt;

